@node "History" "Program History"
@{b}45.7@{ub} (11.3.2011)

 - Added workaround for a bug in OS4 which can cause a crash when a
   requester is opened (bug fixed in intuition.library 53.32).
 - Fixed (VBCC fix) potential system lockup when calling the GM_RENDER
   method in the WarpOS version (e.g. when using Multiview with the
   AfA OS picture.datatype).
 - Added AmiUpdate support.
 - Updated Spanish installer strings.

@{b}45.6@{ub} (5.12.2009)

 - Added workaround for a bug in OS4's datatypes.library
   DTST_MEMORY handling.

@{b}45.5@{ub} (15.11.2009)

 - Added support for flipped row order RLE compressed images.
 - Fixed broken delta handling in the RLE decompression code.
 - Fixed broken 32-bit bitfield compression decoding.
 - Cleaned up WarpDT engine build.
 - Enabled virtual memory usage in OS4 version.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.9a.
 - OS4 version recompiled with latest SDK.

@{b}45.4@{ub} (3.3.2005)

 - Added native AmigaOS 4 version.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.8h.
 - Updated with the latest WarpDT engine build.
 - Minor changes and improvements.
 - Added Polish installer translation.
 - Updated Spanish and French installers.

@{b}45.3@{ub} (9.7.2003)

 - Fixed a problem reading the prefs file from disks using FFS.
 - Fixed another bug which caused bogus evaluation period warnings.
 - Tweaked installer so that it checks for picture.datatype in MOSSYS:
   as well as SYS: when run under MorphOS.

@{b}45.2@{ub} (5.7.2003)

 - Fixed problems with the evaluation period code causing bogus warnings.

@{b}45.1@{ub} (4.7.2003)

 - Fixed problems with decoding bitfield images.
 - Minor optimizations and cleanups.
 - Bumped version to v45 since a stable release has now been reached
   and to reflect the jump to @{"shareware" link "Registration" 0} status.

@{b}44.6@{ub} (19.10.2001)

 - Raised minimum WarpUp requirements from V4 to V5, due to cache flush
   bugs in V4 which cause images to be displayed incorrectly (black
   stripes, corrupt images or completely black images).  These bugs
   affected v44.5.  WarpUp V5 does not have these problems.
 - Cleaned up the WarpOS version, fixing some potential problems that
   could happen when an error occurred.
 - The installer now allows the destination of datatype files to be
   changed.

@{b}44.5@{ub} (24.9.2001)

 - Added options to control the precision/quality of pen allocations for
   when an image is displayed on a palette-based display (8-bit).
 - WarpOS version reworked, now working in a fundamentally different way,
   to completely banish any possibility of cache conflicts.
 - Fixed a bug which could cause a system deadlock if the dither control
   or pen precision options were enabled when using picture.datatype V44
   or higher.
 - Discovered a bug in the CyberGraphX picture.datatype, concerning
   error numbers which would have resulted in an unknown error being
   reported by application software if bitmap allocation failed - added
   workaround.
 - Optimizations made to the dispatch engine.
 - PowerPC versions recompiled with VBCC 0.8.
 - Added French and Spanish strings to the installer.

@{b}44.4@{ub} (15.3.2001)

 - Added preferences options to configure the OS3.5/3.9 @{"dithering control" link "Prefs" 0}
   feature.

@{b}44.3@{ub} (19.2.2001)

 - BMP descriptor no longer insists on BMP files having a .bmp filename 
   extension
 - The dithering disabler feature (for when the OS3.5/3.9 picture.datatype
   is in use on hi/true colour displays) was flawed, since it only worked
   with images that were eventually attached to windows (e.g. Multiview).
   Now dithering will be disabled in all other cases too (e.g. Workbench /
   DOpus backdrops)

@{b}44.2@{ub} (21.1.2001)

 - Speeded up decoding of RLE compressed images (10% faster for PPC)
 - Fixed broken handling of RLE compressed 24-bit BMP files

@{b}44.1@{ub} (17.1.2001)

 - Initial release.
@endnode

